Most of the time, I find it useful to see follow ups to my posts,
which may make corrections, clarifications, or raise furthur 
questions.  Some of the time, my news feed becomes flakey, I'm
away on business, or otherwise unable to read news before the 
articles expire, making it difficult to see and respond to followups.
Therefore, I consider it a common courtesy for anyone to carbon
copy me on responses to my postings, and I'll do the same.

Some times, when especially inflamable material has been posted,
false statements have been made, or I have other reason to believe the 
original author of a posting isn't going to read follow ups and take 
credit for his work, I'll make it an extra point to cc them on any 
posting I make.

